stylometry: Transportation is going from Point A to Point B with nodes and destinations. Transhipment could be a warehouse, a server, a printer, they can all be shipped from different places at different times.  An arc is a pathway from node to node.  Flows are the pathways taken by the arcs.  A transhipment problem could be Dell ordering different parts for all of their processors and waiting for all them to be shipped into their warehouses so that they can all be assembled and sold to the public.  Since Dell doesn't actually make their computers they have to wait for all of the corresponding pieces.
